<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy - Framefox Connect" %>
<div class="min-h-screen bg-slate-50 py-12 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Framefox Connect</p>
    </div>
    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-slate-200 p-8 lg:p-12">
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mb-8">Last updated: <%= Date.today.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %></p>
      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
        <div class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
          <p>
            Framefox Ltd ("we", "our", "us") operates Framefox Connect, a Shopify app that integrates your store with Framefox's professional custom framing and printing fulfilment services. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle personal information in accordance with the Privacy Act 2020 (NZ) and Privacy Act 1988 (Cth), as well as Shopify's Protected Customer Data requirements.
          </p>
          <p>
            By installing or using the Framefox Connect app, you (the "merchant") agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">2. What Information We Collect</h2>
        <div class="mb-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">a. Merchant Information</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            When you install the app, we collect information required to create and manage your account, such as:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-700 space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Contact name and email address</li>
            <li>Shopify store name and URL</li>
            <li>Business name, address, and billing details</li>
            <li>App configuration and usage data (e.g. number of synced products, submitted orders)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">b. Customer Information (Protected Customer Data)</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            To process and fulfil orders, the app may access certain customer details from your Shopify store, including:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-700 space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Customer name and contact information (email, phone, shipping/billing address)</li>
            <li>Order details, product variants, and fulfilment preferences</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mt-3">
            We only access the minimum personal data necessary to provide our service, in line with Shopify's Protected Customer Data requirements.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">3. How We Use Information</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">We use merchant and customer data to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-700 space-y-2 ml-4 mb-4">
          <li>Sync products and order information between Shopify and Framefox's fulfilment system</li>
          <li>Produce and ship custom framed prints to customers on your behalf</li>
          <li>Provide order tracking, production status, and notifications back to Shopify</li>
          <li>Maintain and improve the app's functionality and support</li>
          <li>Communicate updates, invoices, or service notices to merchants</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed font-medium">
          We do not sell, rent, or use customer data for marketing purposes.
        </p>
      </section>
      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">4. Data Storage and Retention</h2>
        <div class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>All data is stored securely on servers located in Australia and/or New Zealand.</li>
            <li>We retain personal information only for as long as required to provide the service or comply with legal and tax obligations.</li>
            <li>Merchant account data is retained until you uninstall the app or request deletion.</li>
            <li>Customer order data is retained for 2 years to allow reprints, warranty support, or dispute resolution.</li>
            <li>Upon request or app uninstallation, we will delete or anonymise personal data unless retention is required by law.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- Section 5 -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">5. Data Security</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          We take reasonable steps to protect information from unauthorised access, use, or disclosure. Our security measures include:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-700 space-y-2 ml-4 mb-4">
          <li>Encrypted data transmission (TLS/SSL) and storage</li>
          <li>Access controls and staff authentication</li>
          <li>Encrypted backups and audit logging</li>
          <li>Segregation of production and test environments</li>
          <li>Incident response processes for data breaches</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          If a data breach is likely to cause serious harm, we will promptly notify affected merchants and, where required, the NZ Privacy Commissioner and/or the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC).
        </p>
      </section>
      <!-- Section 6 -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">6. Data Disclosure</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">We may disclose personal information to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-700 space-y-2 ml-4 mb-4">
          <li>Our fulfilment and logistics partners (for production and delivery)</li>
          <li>Payment and accounting providers (for billing)</li>
          <li>IT infrastructure or data-hosting partners located in Australia or New Zealand</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
          <p>
            All third parties must handle data in compliance with applicable privacy laws and only for the purpose of providing contracted services.
          </p>
          <p>
            We do not transfer data outside Australia or New Zealand unless comparable privacy protections are in place.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- Section 7 -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">7. Your Responsibilities as a Merchant</h2>
        <div class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
          <p>
            As a Shopify merchant, you are the data controller for your customers' information. You must ensure your store's privacy policy discloses that customer data may be shared with Framefox Connect for fulfilment purposes.
          </p>
          <p>
            You must also comply with any applicable privacy obligations in your own jurisdiction (e.g. obtaining consent where required).
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- Section 8 -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">8. Access, Correction, and Deletion Rights</h2>
        <div class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
          <p>
            You and your customers have the right to request access to, correction of, or deletion of personal information held by us.
          </p>
          <p>
            Requests can be made by contacting us (see Section 11). We will respond within a reasonable timeframe in accordance with privacy law requirements.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- Section 9 -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">9. Cookies and Analytics</h2>
        <div class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
          <p>Framefox Connect does not use cookies for tracking customers.</p>
          <p>We may use anonymised analytics within the merchant interface to improve performance and reliability of the app.</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- Section 10 -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <div class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The updated version will be posted within the app and on our website, with the revision date clearly stated.
          </p>
          <p>Material changes will be communicated via email or app notification.</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- Section 11 -->
      <section class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">11. Contact Us</h2>
        <div class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          <p class="mb-2">If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise your privacy rights, please contact:</p>
          <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Framefox Ltd</p>
            <p><a href="https://www.framefox.co.nz/pages/contact" class="text-gray-600 underline hover:text-gray-800">https://www.framefox.co.nz/pages/contact</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- Back Link -->
      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-slate-200 text-center">
        <%= link_to "Back to Login", new_user_session_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 text-sm font-medium" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
